contentrichtext.text: '''King's Men''' or '''Kingsmen''' may refer to: *[[King's Men (TV series)]], Australian police drama series produced over the period 1975-80 *The [[King's Men (Númenor)]], Númenórean royalist faction in J. R. R. Tolkien's writings *The [[King's Men (playing company)]], English company of actors to whom William Shakespeare belonged *[[The Kingsmen]], American rock group *The Kingsmen, Christian Music group formed in 1956, see [[The Kingsmen Quartet]] *The Kingsmen, who were renamed to [[The Statler Brothers]] in the early 1960s *Kingsmen, an a cappella group of [[Columbia College, Columbia University|Columbia College]] NY formed in 1949 *The King's Men, an American vocal quartet formed in 1928 by [[Ken Darby]] *The [[Baganda people]], ethnic group of Buganda sometimes known by this exonym *[[Maceo Parker]] & All The King's Men *The ''Kingsmen,'' [[Penn High School|Penn High School's]] athletic teams' nickname *The ''Kingsmen,'' Nickname of the men's athletic teams at [[Cal Lutheran University]] ==See also== *[[Kingsman]] {{disambiguation}}
